European Stocks Extend Gains as Trichet Suspends Portugal Collateral Rules

-- B y   A n d r e w   R u m m e r
-- 
2011-07-07T12:57:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-07/european-stocks-extend-gains-as-trichet-suspends-portugal-collateral-rules.html
European stocks extended their
advance as European Central Bank President Jean-Claude Trichet
said the bank will suspend collateral rules for  Portugal .  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index rallied 1.1 percent to 277.81 at
1:55 p.m. in  London , the highest level in a month.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew Rummer at 
 arummer@bloomberg.net  